### CSS3 Basics Cheatsheet ###

CSS3 Generator 		http://css3generator.com/
Google Fonts 		https://fonts.google.com/
Font Awesome 		https://fontawesome.com
Compatiblity Check 	https://caniuse.com/

## Box Model ##
float				specifies whether an element should float
clear				control the behavior of floating elements
height				auto, %, px, em, rem
max-height			none, %, px, em, rem
min-height			none, %, px, em, rem
width				auto, %, px, em, rem
max-width			none, %, px, em, rem
min-width			none, %, px, em, rem
margin				top, right, bottom, left
padding				top, right, bottom, left

overflow			specifies what happens if content overflows an elements box
overflow			overflow-y, overflow-x
overflow-style		auto, marquee-line, marquee-block
rotation			angle
rotation-point		position
visiblity			visible, hidden, collapse
display				none, inline, block, inline-block

# Box Shadow #

  #box-shadow {
    -webkit-box-shadow: 3px 3px 3px 3px #000000;
    box-shadow: 3px 3px 3px 3px #000000
  }

## Border ## 
border				width, style, color
border-left			width, style, color
border-right		width, style, color
border-top			width, style, color
border-bottom		width, style, color
border-left-color	color
border-style		none, solid, dotted, dashed ...
 
# Border Image #

	#border-img {
     -webkit-border-image: url(border.png) 30 round;
     -o-border-image: url(border.png) 30 round;
     border-image: url(border.png) 30 round;
	}

# Border Radius #

  #border-round {
    -webkit-border-radius: 5px;
    -moz-border-radius: 5px;
    border-radius: 5px;
	}

## Clearfix Hack – force an element to self-clear its children ##

	.clearfix::after {
	  content: "";
	  clear: both;
	  display: block;
	  visibility: hidden;
	}

## Fonts ##
font-family			"Times New Roman", Times, serif;
font-size			%, em, rem, px
font-weight			normal, bold, bolder, lighter, 100, 200 ...
font-style			normal, italic, oblique, inherit
font-variant		normal, small-caps, inherit
font-stretch		normal, wider, narrower, condensed, semi-condensed, ultra-condensed, expanded, semi-expanded, extra-expanded, ultra-expanded

## Text	##
text-align			start, end, left, right, center, justify
text-align-last		start, end, left, right, center, justify
text-justify		specifies how text should be aligned and spaced
text-decoration		none, underline, overline, line-through, blink
text-transform		none, capitalize, uppercase, lowercase
text-wrap			normal, unrestricted, none, suppress
text-shadow			horizontal length, vertical length, blur radius, color
word-break			Specifies line breaking rules
word-wrap			Allows long words to be able to be broken

# Google Fonts #
	@import url(https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans);

	#title {
	  font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
	}

# Font Awesome #
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="path/to/font-awesome/css/font-awesome.min.css">
	<ul class="fa-ul">
	  <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check-square"></i>List icons</li>
	  <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check-square"></i>can be used</li>
	  <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-spinner fa-spin"></i>as bullets</li>
	  <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-square"></i>in lists</li>
	</ul>

# Multiple Columns #
	columns {
	  -webkit-column-count: 3; /* Chrome, Safari, Opera */
	  -moz-column-count: 3; /* Firefox */
	  column-count: 3;
	  -webkit-column-gap: 40px; /* Chrome, Safari, Opera */
	  -moz-column-gap: 40px; /* Firefox */
	  column-gap: 40px;
	}
